    "The position of the in-cabin sensors used in driver emotion detection is illustrated in Fig. 4.",
    "The application of these methods has made massive progress in effectively monitoring and detecting driver emotions in real time.Comparatively, physiological measurements are more objective and can be measured continuously; however, this measurement is highly intrusive and may have an impact on the measurement result.",
    "Although behavioral measurement is rarely intrusive and can be measured by non-contact sensors, its performance level could decline because people can try to fake or disguise their emotions.",
    "Self-reported scales measure the subjective experience of participants when applied correctly, and provide the opportunity to gain valuable insights about the experienced emotions, but such measurements cannot take place during the study without interruption.",
    "The methods require a relatively long period to perform, potentially resulting in unreliable data."
